review_blob: Wow, what a great beer. Tried it while in Antwerp and what a surprise, tastes like a Sculpin IPA Grapefruit, well not quite buy close! While here the Triples are the best but this reminded me of the great west coast IPAs. Enjoy.

Wow had this on a recent trip to Toronto at a very nice Irish pub Shebeens. Not sure what my Canadian friends think an IPA should taste like because this one is pretty sad. Better bring a 4 pack of green flash ipa with me next time and et them see what a real beer taste like.

Not sure what the other guys were drinking. This is an excellent IPA for those of us on the citrus/pine side of the spectrum with plenty of hops to keep the grape fruit in check. Too bad their double was already sold out,maybe next time..
Nice citrusy taste well balanced by the lighter alcohol content. Hey that's why they say all day ipa!
Nice IPA a little sweet but plenty of hops to balance it out. Found it on tap at Category Three bar and grill in Key Largo, nice.

Cant really call it a beer and hard to believe anyone with a choice would drink this stuff. Unfortunately its the only thing in this guys frig and Im too cheap to pour it out and drink water. Wait Ill drink the water. Wow, this is like the number 1 selling beer in America.....very sad.
Wow, what a winner, pine, citrus, malt and incredible hops. Great job Founders.Too bad, I cant get it in LA but surely will seek it out next time Im in Chi-town.
Dry hopped, malty, thick copper color, nice foam head and a bit of fruit, looks like another great seasonal from Stone. Enjoy
